quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  10,107,"If Allah afflicts you with harm, none can remove it except Him; if He wants good for you, none can withhold His bounty. He grants it to whom He wills of His slaves, and He is the All-Forgiving, the Most Merciful.”",""
  10,108,"Say, “O people, the truth has come to you from your Lord. So whoever accepts guidance, it is only for his own good; and whoever goes astray, it is only for his own loss. I am not a keeper over you.”",""
  10,109,"Follow what is revealed to you, and be patient until Allah passes His judgment, for He is the Best of Judges.",""
  11,1,"Alif Lām Ra<sup>1</sup>. This is a Book whose verses are perfected, then fully explained<sup>2</sup>, from One Who is All-Wise, All-Aware.","[1] See footnote 2:1. [2] i.e., the Qur’an’s verses were made to perfection with neither deficiencies nor contradictions. They were then detailed and explained with truthful news and just rulings."
  11,2,"[Say O Prophet], “Worship none except Allah<sup>3</sup>. Indeed, I am sent to you from Him, as a warner and bearer of glad tidings.","[3] This passage succinctly captures the general purport of the Message: people should worship Allah Almighty alone."
  11,3,"And seek your Lord’s forgiveness and turn to Him in repentance, He will grant you good enjoyment of life for an appointed term and graciously reward the doers of good. But if you turn away, I truly fear for you the punishment of a great Day.",""
  11,4,"To Allah is your return, and He is Most Capable of all things.”",""
  11,5,"Indeed, they lean forward to conceal their feelings from Him, but even when they cover themselves with their clothes, He knows what they conceal and what they reveal, for He is All-Knowing of what is in the hearts.",""
